  image("/assets/figures/05_fingerprint_lever_glue.pdf", width: 78%),
  caption: [Glue circuit size against $n$ for the two plain mechanisms, at each segment count $K$. Both grow $O(n)$---neither flattens---but the product glue (squares) climbs at about a seventh the per-node slope of the sort glue (circles): fitted at $K = 4$, about $2.8$ gates per node against about $19$. The lever cheapens each step of the coverage check rather than making the check asymptotically smaller; the upward shift with $K$ is the $O(K dot D)$ boundary-edge cost both glues share.],
